2026-06-24 20:36:15,893 | INFO     | agent_framework  | trace=e9413d83644f3307bfd9a848836a661f span=6e00de5da8216b65 parent=- | {'role': 'tool', 'parts': [{'type': 'tool_call_response', 'id': 'fc_a07e0f75-83f3-461f-86c8-5a3d562f8654', 'response': 'Based on **FAB Credit Pricing Policy v2.4**, the minimum pricing floor for an **Internal Rating A** AED Corporate Term Loan is defined as a spread over the applicable AED Funds Transfer Pricing (FTP) rate. The exact floor depends on the facility tenor:\n\n| Facility Tenor | Minimum Pricing Floor (over AED FTP) |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **≤ 1 Year** | **85 bps** |\n| **1–3 Years** | **105 bps** |\n| **3–5 Years** | **130 bps** |\n| **> 5 Years** | **165 bps** |\n\n**Key Policy Notes:**\n* **All-In Rate Floor:** The total all-in pricing rate must not fall below the matched-maturity AED FTP rate + the applicable floor spread above `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 3.1]`.\n* **Relationship Value Adjustment:** If the client generates documented cross-sell revenues exceeding **AED 500,000 per annum** across the relationship, the required margin floor may be reduced by up to **25 bps**, subject to relevant credit authority approval `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 2.4]`.\n* **Pricing Exceptions:** Any pricing proposed below these floors requires a formally documented Pricing Exception and approval at the appropriate authority level based on the deviation amount `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 6]`.\n\nFor the exact AED FTP rate to apply, Relationship Managers must obtain the prevailing rate from FAB Treasury at the time of term sheet issuance, as FTP is updated monthly `[FAB_Credit_Pricing_Policy_v2.4 · Section 4.1]`.'}]}
